Update...... after this review, I was contacted by I don't know if it was the owner, manager or who.......the reply stated....there is a sign up in store stating the policy about $2.00 per credit/debit card transaction, I didn't see the sign nor was I looking for a sign.  The person who processed the transaction never stated any such policy either.  I was given a receipt for $5.96 but AFTER I left $2.00 was added on...and $7.96 deducted from my account!!  Bad business!!!

I made a purchase this morning at Farmer Boys Tomato House on 2nd St., I was charged $5.96 and I paid $5.96.  I got an emailed receipt also, after the transaction, they added a $2.00 custom charge without my approval with a total of $7.96!!! $7.96 is the amount that cleared the bank.  I will be pursuing a refund!!!

text: Great locally owned family business!  Very friendly atmosphere.  Nestled in historic downtown Wetumpka!  They always have a great selection of different cuts of meat.  You will not regret trying them!

name: Jessica Joyner
text: This place was amazing! The Gentleman at the counter explained their process and what items were offered beyond their meat selections. I bought some chicken, hamburger patties, and a hash brown casserole. The chicken was hands down the BEST ever! Hamburger patties were good too; (My BF stated they were a little too lean.) however, I wanted to go back the next day and stock up, but they were closed by 3:00 pm on Saturday and they don't reopen till Tuesday. Will go this Friday after work and stock up! It's all local and fresh!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

resp.text: Glad you enjoyed Jessica! You can always add an egg or two to our ground beef to fatten it out if needed. That’s what we do when we take home a leaner pack. 😉 Thanks for supporting our business!

text:
This is the best farmers market I've ever been too! He hand selects some of the best local finds to add to his store.
Like a variety of unique vinegars, blueberry and cucumber are my favorite.
He also has local made cake, the coconut is addicting! So delicious!
He also has shrimp bisque that tastes like you brought the restraunt into your kitchen. Don't forget to grab the homemade cornbread to go with this soup!
I'm making myself hungry thinking of all their delicious products, I'm going to head there now!
